# Frontend architecture (short rules)

Full source of truth: `.ai/memory/architecture.md`. Local Ollama review uses the same rules against git diffs.

## Layers
- `app/` — bootstrap + root router only
- `core/` — config, models, services, auth APIs, utils (no Vue SFCs; never import modules/shared)
- `modules/public` — storefront; `modules/admin` — admin panel
- `shared/` — cross-cutting UI, composables, auth/tenant/subscription stores

## Must follow
- `<script setup lang="ts">`; relative imports (no new `@/` aliases)
- HTTP via `core/services` (or existing `core/auth/*Api`); no raw `fetch` in SFCs for new work
- Public tenant from `/t/:tenantSlug`; admin tenant from auth store context
- Per-tenant tokens: `token:{slug}` via `shared/constants/storageKeys.ts`
- Env only through `envConfig`; types from `core/models`
- Match API contracts; do not invent payload fields or branding colors client-side
